1.title: Muk-Bang
1.plot: Gordo is a dreamer. Hoping to pursue a career of being an actor as well as reunite with his high school crush, Gordo settles in Long Beach, CA. When he has a hard time finding a job, his room mate suggest he try muk-bang-- an internet fad where he eats in front of his webcam as people pay to watch. Gordo must commit to muk-bang or risk leaving California before he can achieve either dream.

2.title: Release
2.plot: Muk-bang is just not cutting it for Gordo. Not only does he dread every minute, but he's not making any money. Still pining after Julia, Gordo sets out to find a new job in her part of town hoping he might run into her. It turns out she's not the only one he runs into.

3.title: The Audition
3.plot: Gordo finally has a job interview that doesn't involve eating in front of people, but as he's getting ready Zietlan surprises him with some even better news-- he got Gordo an audition for a TV commercial. Will Gordo finally get to leave muk-bang behind?

4.title: Lady Fate
4.plot: Gordo is taken by surprise when Blake, Julia's boyfriend calls asking for Gordo's help moving. While aiding the boyfriend of his longtime crush isn't something that greatly excites Gordo, it turns out Blake may be more than he seems.

5.title: The Visit
5.plot: Gordo's finally getting what he's wanted since moving to California-- a little alone time with Julia. But that alone time is because she wants to 'talk' about something. While Gordo isn't too worried about it, everyone around him seems to think he did something wrong. Did he upset Julia in some way?

6.title: Nadir
6.plot: After finally laying to rest his years-long hope of ending up with Julia, Gordo comes home to find the worst thing possible; Zietlan and Stacy in bed. Did Z coerce the recent graduate? Can things possibly get lower for Gordo?
